Desert Ecology

deserts %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = taxa))+
  coord_flip()+
  geom_bar()+
  scale_y_log10()+
  labs(title = "Observations by Taxa",
       x = "Taxa",
       y = "Log count") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = rel(1.5), hjust = 0.5))

  1. Dipodomys merriami is the most frequently sampled animal in the study. How have the number of observations of this species changed over the years included in the study?
deserts %>% 
  filter(species == "merriami") %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  summarize(n=n()) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = n))+
  geom_col()+

       x = "Year",

  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = rel(1.5), hjust = 0.5))
